result.execSummary:
The defendant Kassie Leigh Banie was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Controlled Substances. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 09:04 AM Defendant Kassie Leigh Banie in court.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Banie has received a copy of the complaint. Court reads charges and penalties. Banie understands. Court questions if she has contacted an attorney. Banie has not contacted an attorney and does not feel need for an attorney. Off record, 9:06 AM State makes offer. Back on the record, 9:06 AM. State indicates has extended an offer, to amend sole count to FC ordinance of possession of cocaine, fine of $500 plus costs. Banie agrees. Court amends count one to FC ordinance of possession of cocaine. Banie pleads guilty to the amended charge. Court finds guilty, imposes fine of $500 plus costs - 60 DTP/CO.
